== Sour Cream Mashed Potatoes ==

Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces and place in a #medium pot{} with
enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender,
~{10-12%minutes}. Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid (3⁄4 cup for 4 servings),
then drain.

Return potatoes to #pot{} and mash with half the @sour cream{3%tablespoon} and 
1 TBSP @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) with a #potato masher{} until smooth
and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Taste
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Chicken Pot Pie Filling ==

While potatoes cook, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed, whites and greens
separated), separating whites from greens. Trim, peel, and quarter @carrots{6%ounce}
(trimmed, peeled, quartered lengthwise); thinly slice crosswise into quarter-moons.

Open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
chicken, scallion whites, carrots, and half the @dried thyme{1%teaspoon} 
(all for 4 servings); season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until chicken is browned and nearly cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes} 
(chicken will finish cooking in the next step).

Stir in @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} and @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4). Cook,
stirring constantly, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Sprinkle @flour{1%tablespoon} evenly over chicken mixture; stir to combine.

Add @water{1%cup} (2 cups for 4 servings), @peas{4%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{2},
and remaining sour cream; cook, whisking constantly, until gravy has thickened
and chicken is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} (if gravy seems too thick, add more
water 1 TBSP at a time). Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

== To Serve ==

Divide sour cream mashed potatoes between #shallow bowls{}. Top with crustless
chicken pot pie and garnish with scallion greens. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.